If there was one man that didn’t deserve to be on the losing side at the Nou Camp on Wednesday it was Manchester City goalkeeper Joe Hart.

The England No 1 was in sensational form as he denied Barcelona’s three-pronged attack of Lionel Messi, Neymar and Luis Suarez time and time again.

Hart denied Messi from the penalty spot in the first-leg to give the Citizens a slim chance of progression in the second-leg, but it just wasn’t to be as Ivan Rakitic’s goal secured Barcelona’s spot in the last eight.

